The secretary, leaving the office, picks up the phone:
- Hello, hello. I need Ivan Petrovich. Is he in place?
The secretary didn't even finish listening, hung up the phone and left. The persistent customer calls again, a new employee of the company picks up the phone and the customer immediately without any greeting:
- Is he not in the workshop?
The new employee responds:
- Just a second. I will clarify.
- Colleagues, tell me, does Ovtsekhuyev work here?
